1
00:00:02,288 --> 00:00:06,353
Devotees in the Rupanuga line understand

2
00:00:06,353 --> 00:00:16,090
quite comprehensively, clearly,
thoroughly, with clarity,

3
00:00:16,090 --> 00:00:22,894
that you don’t get any more Kṛṣṇa

4
00:00:22,970 --> 00:00:26,103
than in the presence of Śrīmatī Rādhārāṇī.

5
00:00:26,103 --> 00:00:29,198
[Maximum Krishna]

6
00:00:29,198 --> 00:00:35,039
Just like within this world there are
not only famous people,

7
00:00:35,039 --> 00:00:37,292
but maybe particularly them,

8
00:00:37,292 --> 00:00:43,158
like ‘aiśvaryasya samagrasya vīryasya
yaśasaḥ śriyaḥ’ (Vp: 6.5.47),

9
00:00:43,158 --> 00:00:44,934
who can take it; Bhagavān.

10
00:00:44,934 --> 00:00:51,496
But people will say,
“I can’t really be myself

11
00:00:51,527 --> 00:00:55,366
with these people or that person.

12
00:00:55,366 --> 00:01:00,458
I’m looking for someone 
where I can totally be myself.”

13
00:01:00,458 --> 00:01:03,458
That’s what they hanker for.

14
00:01:03,504 --> 00:01:06,535
Sometimes Guru Mahārāj will say, 
almost humorously, that

15
00:01:06,535 --> 00:01:10,680
“Kṛṣṇa likes to surround Himself
with ignorant people.”

16
00:01:10,680 --> 00:01:17,829
Wait, I thought you said, “Tathā
paramahaṁsānāṁ munīnām amalātmanām

17
00:01:17,829 --> 00:01:21,703
bhakti-yoga-vidhānārthaṁ kathaṁ
paśyema hi striyaḥ”;

18
00:01:21,703 --> 00:01:23,982
only the highest section of liberated souls
(SB 1.8.20).

19
00:01:23,982 --> 00:01:25,389
Now you’re saying that Kṛṣṇa likes to

20
00:01:25,389 --> 00:01:27,304
surround Himself with ignorant people?

21
00:01:27,304 --> 00:01:28,827
What does he mean?

22
00:01:29,189 --> 00:01:30,965
Jñāna-śūnya-bhaktas.

23
00:01:30,965 --> 00:01:41,155
Those who can suppress
Kṛṣṇa's majestic aspect

24
00:01:41,339 --> 00:01:46,940
back to the aprākṛta region where,
as Guru Mahārāj said,

25
00:01:46,940 --> 00:01:52,271
say a king wants to just dress casually.

26
00:01:52,656 --> 00:01:56,635
It doesn't mean he doesn't have a crown
and a sceptre and all these things,

27
00:01:56,635 --> 00:02:02,988
but he just prefers sometimes
to dress in an ordinary way.

28
00:02:03,035 --> 00:02:05,462
Is he still a king?

29
00:02:05,479 --> 00:02:07,532
Of course. He doesn't have to have …

30
00:02:07,655 --> 00:02:09,757
For some people though,
maybe he needs to have the crown,

31
00:02:09,757 --> 00:02:12,226
the sceptre, and the throne 
and everything,

32
00:02:12,226 --> 00:02:15,262
for them to think of him that way.

33
00:02:15,262 --> 00:02:18,887
Here, we have the inverse.
These devotees,

34
00:02:18,887 --> 00:02:24,775
they are so much in love
with Kṛṣṇa, personally,

35
00:02:24,775 --> 00:02:29,564
with His personality, His character traits,
tendencies, etc.

36
00:02:29,795 --> 00:02:37,984
that His majestic divine aspect
is so much eclipsed

37
00:02:37,984 --> 00:02:40,743
by their love and affection,
that it’s sent to the background

38
00:02:40,743 --> 00:02:44,458
and is practically non-existent.

39
00:02:45,438 --> 00:02:50,452
So, that Kṛṣṇa.
We're told Śrīmatī Rādhārāṇī's name.

40
00:02:50,452 --> 00:02:53,727
This is mentioned, quoted,
of particular interest,

41
00:02:53,727 --> 00:02:57,066
in the fourth chapter of Ādi-līlā,

42
00:02:57,066 --> 00:02:59,278
where Kavirāj Goswāmī’s laying the ground

43
00:02:59,278 --> 00:03:01,864
for what is Chaitanya-charitāmṛta.

44
00:03:01,864 --> 00:03:04,791
She is known as Kṛṣṇamayī.

45
00:03:05,483 --> 00:03:07,675
How much Kṛṣṇa is in Her?

46
00:03:07,675 --> 00:03:11,924
Guru Mahārāj said, “It is not that
She’s just full of Kṛṣṇa,

47
00:03:11,924 --> 00:03:15,511
but it is as if anywhere
She casts Her glance,

48
00:03:15,511 --> 00:03:18,862
Kṛṣṇa is manifest.”

49
00:03:18,862 --> 00:03:23,217
So he will say,
“You don‘t get any more Kṛṣṇa,

50
00:03:23,217 --> 00:03:27,330
quality Kṛṣṇa, and quantity Kṛṣṇa,

51
00:03:27,330 --> 00:03:32,233
than Kṛṣṇa at the right hand
of Śrīmatī Rādhārāṇī.”

52
00:03:32,233 --> 00:03:36,080
If you go to Kṛṣṇa direct, even direct,

53
00:03:36,080 --> 00:03:39,590
He won’t fully be Himself in your presence.

54
00:03:39,605 --> 00:03:45,577
He’s only fully Svayam Bhagavān Kṛṣṇa,
to the extreme.

55
00:03:46,099 --> 00:03:49,376
Reality the beautiful. Sweetness.

56
00:03:49,376 --> 00:03:51,833
Love, beauty, charm, sweetness personified.

57
00:03:51,833 --> 00:03:55,194
kandarpa-koṭi-kamanīya-viśeṣa-śobhaṁ 
(Śrī Brahma-saṁhitā. 5.30)

58
00:03:55,194 --> 00:03:59,594
Kṛṣṇa, at the right hand of Śrīmatī Rādhārāṇī.

59
00:04:00,316 --> 00:04:03,706
The way Kṛṣṇa appears with Her

60
00:04:03,706 --> 00:04:08,330
is super-extraordinary
even by Kṛṣṇa's own standards.

61
00:04:08,423 --> 00:04:11,083
Hare Kṛṣṇa.

